Context: The School of Computer Technology at George Brown College offers access to state-of-the-art equipment and expert faculty with industry experience. Their curriculum is regularly updated with real-world input from employers and industry insiders, ensuring skills meet current industry needs. They offer a full-time blockchain certificate program and have partnerships with Microsoft Academy, IBM Academy, and the premier CISCO Networking Academy for industry-recognized certificates (A+, Server+, Linux+, Level 1 Installer, Java Programmer, CCNA, CCSP, CWLSS, and CCNP). They provide a free Entry Advising service for program options, offer information sessions for inquiries, and campus tours. Their contact information is: 416-415-2000, TTY: 1-877-515-5559, ask.george@georgebrown.ca. Their programs and fee requirements are subject to change without notice.
